-- Proposed Hedging Rule Changes May Weaken Chile Peso, Celfin Says
-- B y   S e b a s t i a n   B o y d
-- 2012-05-23T13:30:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/proposed-hedging-rule-changes-may-weaken-chile-peso-celfin-says.html
New rules on currency hedging for
Chilean pension funds may lead to a $2.3 billion unwinding of
hedges, according to a research note from Celfin Capital.  While the proposed changes may lead to short-term demand
for dollars, their impact probably will be transitory, wrote
Santiago-based economist  Cesar Perez .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sebastian Boyd in Santiago at 
 sboyd9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  